MULTI-AWARD-WINNING veteran actress, Dakore Egbuson-Akande has shared how she combines her role as a mother, actress, and businesswoman. The movie star who recently launched her latest business ‘Dakore beauty’ disclosed this in an exclusive chat with The Nation.   Cooking show Sokoyokoto returns     Best Of Nollywood awards: Uzodinma to host 14th Edition     MI Abaga, Chigul, Waje join forces to advocate gender…   She said: “By the grace of God I take it one day at a time you know and I try as much as possible to remember why, why I am doing this? because I care and I want to move my nation, my career, and my family forward.” The ever-busy mum also gave an account of what she had been up to lately saying, “I have been working on films, Castle by Castle, it is coming back. I am so excited about that. I also just shot my own film and also powered by Nigerian Breweries so I am really doing a lot, also I have launched my beauty product ‘Dakore beauty’ so I am a really busy woman and you are going to be seeing more of me on the big screens and Netflix as usual.” Dakore was among the Eko 100 women honored last month, and for the second time in a row, to mark the 2022 International Women’s Day (IWD) by the Lagos state Governor, Babajide Sanwo-Olu.